  "risk_regime": {
    "stance": "risk_on",
    "conviction": 84,
    "rationale": "8 of 10 members are explicitly risk_on with high conviction (Ali 90, Dixon 88, Guy 86, Daren 80, Eddy 80, Miles 80, Jason 75, Kominers 75): pro-crypto US regulatory turn, stablecoin PMF, institutional ETP flows, infra ready for apps. The two abstentions (Thaler, Roughgarden) are research scientists with no market view by design, not dissenters, so they don't offset the bullish weight. The posture is uniformly fundamentals/adoption-driven and long-horizon, and explicitly selective \u2014 paired with strong risk-off conviction on speculation, memecoins, and company-backed tokens.",
    "provenance": "grounded"
  },
  "notes": "Weights coverage x conviction; splits discounted toward neutral. STRONGEST/BROADEST: ai-crypto (6/10) and stablecoins (5/10), near-unanimous and high-conviction, plus a shared token taxonomy (network tokens ETH/BTC/SOL/UNI good; company-backed/disguised-equity FTT + memecoins bad). DELIBERATELY NEUTRALIZED SPLITS: (1) crypto-policy-regulation \u2014 4/10 coverage but stance_dispersion 1.0, mean_stance_sign 0; treated as NEUTRAL not listed, since disagreement is largely framing (Dixon +92 / Miles +85 see clarity as the unlock; Ali -45 ideological wariness; Jason -35 has effectively flipped to optimism). House read: constructive-but-mixed tailwind. (2) restaking \u2014 bullish as a primitive vs systemic-risk flag \u2192 low-conviction neutral. (3) on-chain-adoption \u2014 split because Matsuoka holds it as BOTH his signature opportunity AND chief worry (dormant holders, gameable active-address metrics); netted out into notes rather than double-listed. (4) incentive-design \u2014 split (constructive token value-accrual vs bearish demand-side incentives). FADED LONE VIEWS: many coverage=1 items (decentralized-energy, light-clients, gaming, prediction-markets, health-data-markets, crypto-insurance, modular-da, Thaler's SNARK sub-theses) carry real individual conviction but were down-weighted; the most decision-relevant lone caution (Thaler on SNARK production-readiness) is retained explicitly. TOKEN signal is thin and category-driven: Kominers/Miles/Eddy disclaim price calls and speak in token CATEGORIES, so token convictions reflect classification/legitimacy, not price targets. Thaler and Roughgarden contribute essentially no token or market-direction views by design."
}